Subject: [PATCH 14/42] =?UTF-8?q?inline-3d(#625):=20quiet=20bring-up=20dia?=
 =?UTF-8?q?gnostics=20=E2=80=94=20success=20one-shots=20LOG(ERROR)=20->=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?VLOG(1)?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The per-frame hot-path traces were already stripped in B4b/B4c; this quiets the
remaining success-path one-shot bring-up confirmations so a default (non-verbose)
chrome is silent, while keeping them available under --v=1 for the ongoing B4d
(zero-copy) + look-around validation. Error-path LOG(ERROR) are unchanged (real
failure logging). Also drops the B2a/B2c.2/PASSED scaffolding phase markers from
the messages.

Converted (9 sites): weave provider registered (chrome + shell gpu clients),
weave client init/display-info/PFNs/bindWindow-success (displayxr_weave_client.cc),
weave-input-ready + canvas-tex (displayxr_weave_gpu.cc), and the DComp root-pass
weave marker (skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc). bindWindow failure kept as
LOG(ERROR). Re-verified: weave still fires under default flags (no 0x80070057),
default log now quiet.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 chrome/gpu/chrome_content_gpu_client.cc       |  2 +-
 .../browser/displayxr_weave_client.cc         | 33 ++++++++++---------
 .../displayxr/gpu/displayxr_weave_gpu.cc      | 12 +++----
 .../skia_output_surface_impl_on_gpu.cc        |  6 ++--
 content/shell/gpu/shell_content_gpu_client.cc |  2 +-
 5 files changed, 28 insertions(+), 27 deletions(-)

diff --git a/chrome/gpu/chrome_content_gpu_client.cc b/chrome/gpu/chrome_content_gpu_client.cc
index fcb8556287010..8937f73875844 100644
--- a/chrome/gpu/chrome_content_gpu_client.cc
+++ b/chrome/gpu/chrome_content_gpu_client.cc
@@ -157,7 +157,7 @@ void ChromeContentGpuClient::PostCompositorThreadCreated(
     weave_gpu_ = std::make_unique<displayxr::DisplayXRWeaveGpu>();
     weave_gpu_->Bind();
     viz::SetDisplayXRWeaveProvider(weave_gpu_.get());
-    LOG(ERROR) << "[DisplayXR] B2c GPU weave provider registered";
+    VLOG(1) << "[DisplayXR] inline-3D GPU weave provider registered";
   }
 #endif
 }
diff --git a/components/displayxr/browser/displayxr_weave_client.cc b/components/displayxr/browser/displayxr_weave_client.cc
